cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.PF 

This paper focuses on the scalability issues in P2P systems, which are typically studied in the computer networks (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper also proposes models to compute achievable throughput, which falls under the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper discusses the behavior of P2P swarming systems, which can be considered a complex system and falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes new mechanisms to improve performance, which can be considered a performance analysis (cs.PF) sub-category.
